---
import SiteLayout from '../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import Icon from '../../components/Icon.astro';
import { reference, referenceSections } from '../../data/reference';
---
<SiteLayout title="Reference — Design / index" description="Browse the local design engine: foundations, components, patterns, quality rules, governance, and platform contracts." active="docs">
  <section class="reference-hero page-frame"><div><p class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-rule"></span> The local engine</p><h1>The whole system,<br /><em>made readable.</em></h1><p>Every canonical contract is indexed here from the repository itself. Read the rendered explanation, then open the source when the decision needs full context.</p></div><div class="reference-hero-stat"><strong>{reference.length}</strong><span>reference documents</span><small>local / versioned / source-linked</small></div></section>
  <div class="reference-shell page-frame"><aside class="reference-sidebar" aria-label="Reference sections"><div class="sidebar-heading"><span class="eyebrow">REFERENCE</span><span class="sidebar-total">{reference.length} docs</span></div><nav class="sidebar-nav"><a class="sidebar-link is-selected" href="/reference/" data-section="All">All documents <span>{reference.length}</span></a>{referenceSections.map((section) => <a class="sidebar-link" href={`/reference/?section=${encodeURIComponent(section)}`} data-section={section}>{section} <span>{reference.filter((item) => item.section === section).length}</span></a>)}</nav><div class="sidebar-note"><span class="note-dot"></span><p>The Markdown files remain the source of truth. This route is a static reading layer.</p></div></aside><section class="reference-content"><div class="reference-toolbar"><label class="search-field"><Icon name="search" size={17} /><input id="reference-search" type="search" placeholder="Search the reference" autocomplete="off" /><kbd>/</kbd></label><span id="reference-result-count" class="result-count">{reference.length} docs</span></div><div class="reference-grid" id="reference-grid">{reference.map((item) => <a class="reference-card" href={`/reference/${item.slug}/`} data-section={item.section} data-search={`${item.title} ${item.section} ${item.description} ${item.source} ${item.status}`}><div class="reference-card-meta"><span>{item.section}</span><span class={`status status-${item.status.toLowerCase()}`}>{item.status}</span></div><h2>{item.title}</h2><div class="reference-card-footer"><code>{item.source}</code><span><Icon name="arrow" size={15} /></span></div></a>)}</div><p id="reference-empty" class="empty-results" hidden>No reference documents match that search. Try a broader term.</p></section></div>
  <script>
    const search = document.querySelector('#reference-search');
    const cards = [...document.querySelectorAll('.reference-card')];
    const resultCount = document.querySelector('#reference-result-count');
    const empty = document.querySelector('#reference-empty');
    const links = [...document.querySelectorAll('[data-section]')].filter((element) => element.classList.contains('sidebar-link'));
    const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
    let activeSection = params.get('section') || 'All';
    const update = () => { const query = search.value.trim().toLowerCase(); let visible = 0; cards.forEach((card) => { const show = (!query || card.dataset.search.toLowerCase().includes(query)) && (activeSection === 'All' || card.dataset.section === activeSection); card.hidden = !show; if (show) visible += 1; }); resultCount.textContent = `${visible} ${visible === 1 ? 'doc' : 'docs'}`; empty.hidden = visible !== 0; links.forEach((link) => link.classList.toggle('is-selected', link.dataset.section === activeSection)); };
    links.forEach((link) => link.addEventListener('click', (event) => { event.preventDefault(); activeSection = link.dataset.section; history.replaceState({}, '', activeSection === 'All' ? '/reference/' : `/reference/?section=${encodeURIComponent(activeSection)}`); update(); }));
    search.addEventListener('input', update);
    update();
  </script>
</SiteLayout>
